                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1"
                        >Ekvall, Henry</persName>/53: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State (<persName type="from"
                            >Carr</persName>) to the Minister in China (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 5, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>362. Your 1234, November 5, 2 p.m. Department feels that you should send to
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SEF1">Stanton</persName> at once a
                    paraphrase of Department’s 361, November 4, 5 p.m. with directions to present
                    full demands to the local Chinese authorities and at the same time to inform the
                    representatives of the Nanking Government at Sian of demands; and that you
                    should instruct <persName>Peck</persName> to file for record with Nanking
                    authorities the full demands. Department feels also that the question of
                    accepting any offer made by Chinese authorities to pay immediate compensation
                    for American property losses suffered remains open pending <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_SEF1">Stanton</persName>’s presentation of full
                    demands and his report with regard to the attitude of the Chinese
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
